<h1>The Shibe World (status: alpha test)</h1>
<img src="the_shibe_world_images/cover.png"/>

<h2>What is it?</h2>
<p>The shibe world is a mmo rpg that accepts dogecoin transactions in-game. It is currently under a playable alpha test.</p>
<img width="700" src="the_shibe_world_images/screenshot.png"/>

<h2>How to play</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
    Download the <a href="https://www.themanaworld.org/downloads.php">manaplus client</a>.
  </li>
  <li>
    Add a new server pointing to 178.62.248.192 and the port 6901.
    <br/>
    <img width="700" src="the_shibe_world_images/tuto_add_server.png"/>
  </li>
  <li>
    Download the patches, register and play!
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>How to use Dogecoin in-game</h2>
<p>Use the following commands the chat and see the results on the debug tab:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    Shows help:
    <br/>
    <b>@doge help</b>
  </li>
  <li>
    Shows your deposit address:
    <br/>
    <b>@doge deposit</b>
  </li>
  <li>
    Shows your balance:
    <br/>
    <b>@doge balance</b>
  </li>
  <li>
    Sends dogecoins to another player:
    <br/>
    <b>@doge tip [character name] [amount]</b>
  </li>
  <li>
    Sends dogecoins to an address:
    <br/>
    <b>@doge withdraw [destination address] [amount]</b>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>How to develop</h2>
<p>Do The Mana World <a href="https://wiki.themanaworld.org/index.php/Dev:How_to_Develop">How to Develop</a> tutorial using the following repos:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <a href="git://github.com/rosalila/tmwa.git">git://github.com/rosalila/tmwa.git</a> instead of <a href="git://github.com/themanaworld/tmwa.git">git://github.com/themanaworld/tmwa.git</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="git://github.com/rosalila/tmwa-server-data.git">git://github.com/rosalila/tmwa-server-data.git</a> instead of <a href="git://github.com/themanaworld/tmwa-server-data.git">git://github.com/themanaworld/tmwa-server-data.git</a>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>The Mana World</h2>
<p>The Shibe World is based on The Mana World. Find more about the project on their <a href="https://www.themanaworld.org/">website</a> and support them on <a href="http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=232178669">steam greenlight</a>.</p>
